<p itemprop="description">A service designer designs end-to-end services that meet user needs and organisational objectives. They understand complex user journeys, map service ecosystems, and work collaboratively across disciplines to deliver seamless, accessible services that work for citizens and government alike.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design comprehensive end-to-end services across multiple channels and touchpoints</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Conduct service design research including user interviews and stakeholder mapping</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create service blueprints, journey maps, and service prototypes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Facilitate co-design workshops and service improvement sessions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with policy, operations, and delivery teams on service implementation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure services are accessible and inclusive across all touchpoints</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Measure and iterate service performance based on user feedback</li>
    </ul>
</section>

